subtitle: 1 missed period
title: How do I know I’m pregnant?
content:
Created by BabyCenter

Are you pregnant? How can you tell? A sure sign is a missed period, but you may find it hard to remember the date of your last period.

**Do you have any of these signs of pregnancy?**

•	Your breasts look and feel different 

•	You notice some spots of blood in your underwear 

•	You feel nauseated, sick to your stomach

•	You need to urinate more than usual 

•	You miss a period

If you think you are pregnant, it is best to see a healthcare provider. The earlier you find out, the sooner you can start planning for your new baby. A healthcare provider will also be able to give you advice and help while you are pregnant.


They will weigh you, check your blood pressure and test your urine. 

Worried about seeing a healthcare provider? Ask a family member or someone you trust to go with you.
